Authorities recovered the 18 rhino horns weighing 43 kilograms during a routine search. JOHANENSBURG The Hawks have arrested a Chinese national for dealing in rhino horn worth nearly R7 million at the OR Tambo International Airport.Authorities recovered the 18 rhino horns weighing 43 kilograms during a routine search.The 28-year-old man was in transit from Namibia on his way to Hong Kong.The Hawks Ndibhuwo Mulamu says the suspect will appear in court tomorrow. Upon arrival, they discovered that the Chinese national had with him, in his traveling bags, about 43kg rhino horns, which were counted to be a number of 18. (Edited by Leeto M Khoza)